profile:
K H Davis Engineering Consultants Ltd are Toronto based Structural Engineers and Home Designers specializing in Houses - Watch for us on HGTV Income Property, Leave it to Bryan, Disaster DIY.  We provide structural engineering services to homeowners, architects and builders.  KH Davis Engineering Consultants Ltd prepares building permit plans for renovation and additions to all types of houses, removing bearing walls, basement lowering, fixing problems in older homes, expert witness testimony and advocacy for homeowners dealing with construction problems.  Members of Professional Engineers of Ontario and BILD.
Structural Related Construction Services also offered through our sister company K H Davis Construction Ltd. If you need a structural engineer, please contact us today!
service_area: Greater Toronto Area primarily, but we also service clients regularly as far to the west at Kitchener Waterloo/Hamilton and as far to the east as Oshawa/Ajax, and North into the Orillia/Muskoka region.
products:
Design, Permit Plans, and Construction Services for:
- Removing Load Bearing Walls
- Basement Underpinning (lowering) Design
- Secondary dwelling units
- General Structural Engineering for all types of houses and small buildings
- Architectural design for additions, renovations, and new houses
- Structural Engineering for any type of building project - residential, commercial, industrial, institutional - but we generally don't do structural engineering for very large buildings and condominium projects - we specialize in small projects which involve some sort of structural changes to a building or a building addition.  We design many new homes each year for architects and builders.
services:
- Structural Engineering Design
- Full Building Permit plans for Part 9 Buildings - Generally having 3 stories or less, and a total square footage of less than about 1800 sq. m. ( 18,000 square feet )
- Site Visits to consult on structural problems with houses - sloping floors, cracked walls, foundation settlement problems.
- Advocacy for Homeowners who have run into problems with a construction project.

profile:
We design new homes, additions, renovations and commercial buildings, and provide green solutions in the Greater Toronto Area, York Region and Southern Ontario. 

Established in 1996 and located in downtown Toronto, our work focuses on the specifics of the relationship of building to site, the enhancement of user experience, and the presence of structure and material in the experience of the building. Architectural solutions are developed that employ an economy of means to achieve spatial richness within straightforward construction and form. Our design work is bolstered by extensive construction experience gained over twenty years as a construction contractor, and is informed by the practical aspects of sustainable design, a practice we began in the late 70's.

profile:
KBK Architects Inc. is a proud Canadian multidisciplinary Architectural & Engineering firm, licensed with the Ontario Association of Architects (OAA) and the Professional Engineers of Ontario (PEO), and BCIN Certified with the Ministry of Municipal Affairs and Housing and is bound by their respective Codes of Professional Conduct. 
 
Our full time in-house team of Architects, Professional Engineers and team of licensed Certified Designers have extensive expertise in many different aspects of residential & commercial projects. We offer complete Planning, Architectural, Structural & Mechanical Engineering, Construction Management and Building Permit Application Services in Toronto and the GTA. KBK Architects Inc. will assist you every step of the way. 
  
Our Small projects division has extensive experience in Interior Alterations projects such as Load Bearing Wall Removal Design, Basement Apartment Design, Below Grade Steps Design, Detached or Attached Garage Design. Let us help you with complexities of dealing with zoning bylaws and City requirements.  
 
If you are facing a Stop order or a Notice to Comply situation, please email us at info@kbkarchitects.ca or give us call 1(800)203-7010 to discuss your situation and see how we can help you resolve the matter to avoid any penalties. 
 
KBK Architects Inc. Planning Division specializes in Minor Variance and Committee of Adjustment Representations, Zoning By-law amendments, and feasibility studies for construction projects.
 
For more information please visit our website www.kbkarchitects.ca
 
If you have any questions about our services or would like discuss a new project please call 1(800)203-7010 and one of our team members will be more than happy to assist you.
services:
Services Tailor made for homeowners involve alterations, additions, renovations, and new building design- Custom House Design for new builds, for houses of all sizes and styles such as: 
- House Additions such as small additions to houses, house top ups, complete interior and exterior renovation and updating.
- Planning applications for Minor Variances, Committee of Adjustment, consent, subdivisions, and severance applications.
- Construction Management; our Team will manage the construction of project including subcontractor selection, material acquisition, inspections, contract administration, and completion of your project up to closing.
- Construction phase administration, we administer projects designed by our team to assist our clients in reviewing the contract document with the builders, reviewing progress of work, issuing certificates of payment, and addressing all concerns during the construction phase.
- Architect/ Engineer Site Review, General Review, and construction assistance.
- Interior alterations such as redesigning the floor plan, modernizing the flow of your layout, structural alterations, finishing unfinished spaces, underpinning and improvement of foundations, and renovation projects for residential buildings.
- Accessory dwelling units, also known and Secondary suites and basement apartments.
- Exterior Works: Decks, patios, cabanas, walk outs, below grade steps, canopies, pools, and backyard projects.


*** Our Services for business owners include the following project types:

- Interior Alterations to existing commercial units.
- Change of Use.
- Architect/ Engineer Site Review, General Review, and construction assistance.
- Construction phase administration, we administer projects designed by our team to assist our clients in reviewing the contract document with the builders, reviewing progress of work, issuing certificates of payment, and addressing all concerns during the construction phase.

After we design your house, we can offer you construction quotes from several reliable contractors we work with, and we will manage the acquisition, contract management, inspections, and collaboration with sub-contractors professionally until construction closing.
